urlText: Phillip St, temporary bus stop closure
content:
From 9pm Friday 19 February to 6am Monday 22 February 2021, Parramatta Light Rail work will the intersection of Phillip and Church Streets.

The bus stop Phillip St after Church St (2150377) will be closed and the stop temporarily relocated on George St after Church St.
subtitle: Phillip St, temporary bus stop closure

urlText: Castlereagh St, temporary bus stop closure
content:
From midnight Saturday 20 February to midnight Monday 22 February 2021, Tower crane works will close Castlereagh St between King St and Park St.

The following bus stop closures will be in place:
  • Bus stops Martin Place, Castlereagh St, Stand G (2000183) and Martin Place, Castlereagh St, Stand H (200077) will be closed. The alternative stop will be Martin Place Station, Elizabeth St, Stand F (200081).
  • David Jones, Castlereagh St, Stand A (200079) and David Jones, Castlereagh St, Stand B (200078). The alternative stop will be St James Station, Elizabeth St (200045).
  • Castlereagh St before Bathurst St (200069). The alternative stop is Hyde Park, Elizabeth ST, Stand A (2000167).
Please note that bus route 320 towards Mascot is not affected by this closure and will continue to use bus stop Castlereagh St before Bathurst St (200069).
subtitle: Castlereagh St, temporary bus stop closure

properties.speechText: From midnight Saturday 20th February to midnight Monday 22th February 20-21, Tower crane works will close Castlereagh Street between King Street and Park Street.

urlText: Park St, temporary bus stop closure
content:
From 11pm Saturday 27 February to midnight Monday 1 March 2021, Sydney Metro work will close below bus stops on Park St:

  • Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand G (2000426) will close, affecting route 311 to Railway Square and 324 and 325 towards Watsons Bay. The alternative stop will be Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand H (2000249).
  • Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand K (2000252) will close. The alternative stop for all services will be Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand J (2000425).
subtitle: Park St, temporary bus stop closure

urlText: Buses replace trains between Gosford and Wyong
content:
Monday 1 to Thursday 4 March
  • Nightly from 9.10pm until 3.55am, buses replace trains from Gosford to Wyong.
  • Trains run to the normal timetable from Central to Gosford but run up to 30 minutes later than normal from Wyong to Newcastle Interchange.
  • The last direct train leaves Central at 19:15 and arrives Newcastle Interchange at 22:01.
  • Nightly from 9.50pm until 2am, buses replace trains from Wyong to Gosford.
  • Trains run to the normal timetable from Newcastle Interchange to Wyong, but run up to 25 minutes later than normal from Gosford to Central.
  • The last direct train leaves Newcastle Interchange at 19:45 and arrives Central at 22:39.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
11CN: Wyong, then Tuggerah, Gosford and return
12CN: Wyong, then all stations to Gosford and return
subtitle: Buses replace trains between Gosford and Wyong
